# 2026-05-22: api/ folder excluded from Vercel deploys.
#
# Why: every Vercel deploy was failing at "Provisioning Integrations" because
# the tradewithvarsha-db Turso integration couldn't provision a DB branch
# (likely the TURSO_AUTH_TOKEN got rotated and the integration's stored
# credential went stale). Result: 2+ days of failed deploys → no fixes live.
#
# Public-mode Vercel doesn't need auth or any serverless functions. The site
# is a static SPA fed by snapshots from GitHub raw URLs (no backend round-
# trip). Auth lives on the localhost dev server only. By excluding api/,
# Vercel auto-detection stops creating functions, the Turso integration
# stops being invoked, and deploys succeed.
#
# Also fixes the 1M Function Invocations quota warning — zero functions
# means zero invocations.
api/
server/
.claude/
*.log
